\section{Introduction}\label{sec:Introduction}




The transport of energy in the ocean by internal gravity waves is vital for thermohaline circulation, ocean mixing, and the ocean's overall energy budget~\cite*{munk98,alford03,wunsch04}. The rate at which internal wave energy is transported through an area is given by the baroclinic energy flux,

