\section{Implementation of Matlab GUI {\it EnergyFlux}}
\label{sec:gui}

To aid in the implementation of this method, a graphical user interface {\it EnergyFlux} was developed for Matlab.  This software is available in the supplemental materials along with a tutorial for use.  The GUI requires only the density perturbation field over a number of time steps, the corresponding coordinates, buoyancy frequency, and time step size.  The GUI allows for the implementation of the data buffering procedure presented in appendix~\ref{sec:cropped} and the selection of what range of horizontal modes to consider in the calculation.




